HEADWORD: Isabella color
<hw>Is`a*bel"la
col"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <ety>[Said to be named from the
Spanish princess <etsep>Isabella</etsep>, daughter of king
<person>Philip II.</person>, in allusion to the color assumed by her
shift, which she wore without change from 1601 to 1604, in consequence
of a vow made by her.]</ety> <def>A brownish yellow color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

